  "usageInstructions": "Instructions",
  "batchCopyGuide": "Batch Configuration Distribution Guide:",
  "batchCopyGuideStep1": "1. Select Consul Config - Choose the Consul instance from the dropdown",
  "batchCopyGuideStep2": "2. Set source and target suffix - Specify which environment to copy from/to (e.g. from V2.5.1 to 147)",
  "batchCopyGuideStep2b": "2.1 If source and target suffixes are the same, enable \"Replace In Place\" — this updates existing keys instead of creating new ones",
  "batchCopyGuideStep3": "3. Enable/disable recursive copy - Choose whether to copy all child keys",
  "batchCopyGuideStep4": "4. (Optional) Configure replacement rules - Supports Tag, Server, Branch, SubmoduleBranch replacements. The system matches key-value pair format precisely, e.g. tag: \"V2.5.0\" → tag: \"V2.5.1\", supporting both quoted and unquoted values:",
  "batchCopyGuideStep4Tag": "Tag Replacement: replace version tags, e.g. V2.5.0 → test10",
  "batchCopyGuideStep4Server": "Server Replacement: replace server addresses, e.g. 192.168.1.231 → 192.168.1.111",
  "batchCopyGuideStep4Branch": "Branch Replacement: replace branch names",
  "batchCopyGuideStep4SubmoduleBranch": "SubmoduleBranch Replacement: replace submodule branches",
  "batchCopyGuideStep5": "5. (Optional) Configure advanced replacement rules - Use text or regex replacement for more complex scenarios",
  "batchCopyGuideStep6": "6. Click \"Execute Batch Config Distribution\" - Start the batch configuration operation",
  "batchCopyGuideStep7": "7. View results - The number of successful/failed keys will be displayed in the result area",
  "batchCopyGuideExample": "Example:",
  "batchCopyGuideExampleText": "Copy all project V2.5.1 environment configs to 147 environment: plugin/*/V2.5.1 → plugin/*/147",
  "batchCopyGuideNote": "Note: The system matches key-value pairs precisely and will not replace unrelated content.",
